    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Jeremiah",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 10,
        "summary": "Learn not the way of other nations\u2014Their gods are idols and molten images\u2014The Lord is the true and living God.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "Hear ye the word which the Lord speaketh unto you, O house of Israel:",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Thus saith the Lord, Learn not the way of the heathen, and be not dismayed at the signs of heaven; for the heathen are dismayed at them.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Heathen.",
                        "start": 46,
                        "end": 53
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For the customs of the people are vain: for one cutteth a tree out of the forest, the work of the hands of the workman, with the axe.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 40:19 (19\u201320); 44:12. TG\u00a0Traditions of Men.",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 15
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 30,
                        "end": 33
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 44,
                        "end": 47
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "They deck it with silver and with gold; they fasten it with nails and with hammers, that it move not.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "They are upright as the palm tree, but speak not: they must needs be borne, because they cannot go. Be not afraid of them; for they cannot do evil, neither also is it in them to do good.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 46:7.",
                        "start": 69,
                        "end": 74
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 5,
                        "end": 8
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 161,
                        "end": 166
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Forasmuch as there is none like unto thee, O Lord; thou art great, and thy name is great in might.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 71:19.",
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 31
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 13,
                        "end": 21
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 56,
                        "end": 59
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 80,
                        "end": 82
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Who would not fear thee, O King of nations? for to thee doth it appertain: forasmuch as among all the wise men of the nations, and in all their kingdoms, there is none like unto thee.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Esth. 1:13.",
                        "start": 102,
                        "end": 106
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ex. 8:10 (8\u201310); Ps. 89:6.",
                        "start": 168,
                        "end": 172
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 107,
                        "end": 110
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 154,
                        "end": 162
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "But they are altogether brutish and foolish: the stock is a doctrine of vanities.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 55,
                        "end": 57
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Silver spread into plates is brought from Tarshish, and gold from Uphaz, the work of the workman, and of the hands of the founder: blue and purple is their clothing: they are all the work of cunning men.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 115:4.",
                        "start": 183,
                        "end": 187
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 124:84.",
                        "start": 191,
                        "end": 198
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 147,
                        "end": 149
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 171,
                        "end": 174
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 199,
                        "end": 203
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "But the Lord is the true God, he is the living God, and an everlasting king: at his wrath the earth shall tremble, and the nations shall not be able to abide his indignation.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Josh. 22:34; D&C 76:1.",
                        "start": 25,
                        "end": 28
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "JS\u2014H 1:17.",
                        "start": 40,
                        "end": 50
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Kingdom of God, in Heaven.",
                        "start": 71,
                        "end": 75
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Indignation of.",
                        "start": 162,
                        "end": 173
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 13,
                        "end": 15
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 33,
                        "end": 35
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Thus shall ye say unto them, The gods that have not made the heavens and the earth, even they shall perish from the earth, and from under these heavens.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Idolatry.",
                        "start": 33,
                        "end": 37
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 84,
                        "end": 88
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "He hath made the earth by his power, he hath established the world by his wisdom, and hath stretched out the heavens by his discretion.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "When he uttereth his voice, there is a multitude of waters in the heavens, and he causeth the vapours to ascend from the ends of the earth; he maketh lightnings with rain, and bringeth forth the wind out of his treasures.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0storehouses.",
                        "start": 211,
                        "end": 220
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 28,
                        "end": 36
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Every man is brutish in his knowledge: every founder is confounded by the graven image: for his molten image is falsehood, and there is no breath in them.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Idolatry.",
                        "start": 81,
                        "end": 86
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 24,
                        "end": 27
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 109,
                        "end": 111
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 127,
                        "end": 135
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "They are vanity, and the work of errors: in the time of their visitation they shall perish.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0mockery.",
                        "start": 33,
                        "end": 39
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 56:1.",
                        "start": 62,
                        "end": 72
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 5,
                        "end": 8
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 17,
                        "end": 20
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The portion of Jacob is not like them: for he is the former of all things; and Israel is the rod of his inheritance: The Lord of hosts is his name.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 957
                    }
                ],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 21,
                        "end": 23
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 46,
                        "end": 48
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 67,
                        "end": 74
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 86,
                        "end": 88
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 135,
                        "end": 137
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Gather up thy wares out of the land, O inhabitant of the fortress.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For thus saith the Lord, Behold, I will sling out the inhabitants of the land at this once, and will distress them, that they may find it so.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 135,
                        "end": 141
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Woe is me for my hurt! my wound is grievous: but I said, Truly this is a grief, and I must bear it.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 68,
                        "end": 70
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "My tabernacle is spoiled, and all my cords are broken: my children are gone forth of me, and they are not: there is none to stretch forth my tent any more, and to set up my curtains.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Jer. 4:20.",
                        "start": 3,
                        "end": 13
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 98,
                        "end": 101
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 107,
                        "end": 115
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "For the pastors are become brutish, and have not sought the Lord: therefore they shall not prosper, and all their flocks shall be scattered.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Shepherd.",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 15
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Behold, the noise of the bruit is come, and a great commotion out of the north country, to make the cities of Judah desolate, and a den of dragons.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Jer. 1:14; 4:6; 6:1.",
                        "start": 73,
                        "end": 78
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0jackals.",
                        "start": 139,
                        "end": 146
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 126,
                        "end": 129
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "O Lord, I know that the way of man is not in himself: it is not in man that walketh to direct his steps.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 20:24.",
                        "start": 24,
                        "end": 27
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 35,
                        "end": 37
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 54,
                        "end": 59
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "O Lord, correct me, but with judgment; not in thine anger, lest thou bring me to nothing.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Punish.",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 15
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ezek. 34:16; 1\u00a0Ne. 22:21.",
                        "start": 29,
                        "end": 37
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Pour out thy fury upon the heathen that know thee not, and upon the families that call not on thy name: for they have eaten up Jacob, and devoured him, and consumed him, and have made his habitation desolate.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Eph. 6:4 (1\u20134).",
                        "start": 68,
                        "end": 76
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            }
        ]
    }
}